<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Iostream on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/iostream/</link><description>Recent content in Iostream on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/iostream/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::ios_base::failure - stream error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ios-base-failure/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ios-base-failure/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdios_basefailure---stream-error"&gt;std::ios_base::failure - stream error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::ios_base::failure&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when an I/O stream operation fails. This includes file errors, format errors, and internal stream failures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: File not found
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ifstream file(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;nonexistent.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;file &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; value; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// may throw ios_base::failure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Format mismatch
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;stringstream ss(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ss &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; val; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// format error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Permission denied
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ofstream file(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/root/test.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-stream-state"&gt;Fix 1: Check stream state&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ifstream file(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;file.is_open()) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Failed to open file&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-after-read"&gt;Fix 2: Check after read&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; val;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ss &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; val) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// success
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Format error&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-exception-mask"&gt;Fix 3: Use exception mask&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ifstream file(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;file.exceptions(std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ifstream&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;failbit &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ifstream&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;badbit);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; file &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; value;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ios_base&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;failure&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Stream error: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; e.what() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/fstream-error/"&gt;std::fstream - file stream error&lt;/a&gt; — file stream error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ifstream-error/"&gt;std::ifstream - input file error&lt;/a&gt; — input file error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ofstream-error/"&gt;std::ofstream - output file error&lt;/a&gt; — output file error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::ios_base::failure — Stream Exception Handling Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ios-failure-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ios-failure-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdios_basefailure--stream-exception-handling-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::ios_base::failure — Stream Exception Handling Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::ios_base::failure&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a stream I/O operation fails and &lt;code&gt;exceptions()&lt;/code&gt; has been configured to throw on &lt;code&gt;badbit&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;failbit&lt;/code&gt;. Streams do not throw by default — they set error flags instead. When you enable exception throwing via &lt;code&gt;exceptions()&lt;/code&gt;, any stream error triggers this exception.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdios_basefailure-occurs"&gt;Why std::ios_base::failure Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include reading from a non-existent or already-closed file stream, writing to a read-only stream, formatting errors (e.g., extracting an int from &amp;ldquo;hello&amp;rdquo;), calling &lt;code&gt;exceptions()&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;badbit | failbit&lt;/code&gt; flags, and stream state corruption from bad I/O operations.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::ios_base::failure — Stream I/O Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ios-failure/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ios-failure/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdios_basefailure--stream-io-error-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::ios_base::failure — Stream I/O Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::ios_base::failure&lt;/code&gt; (also &lt;code&gt;std::ios_base::failure&lt;/code&gt;) is thrown when a stream I/O operation fails and &lt;code&gt;exceptions()&lt;/code&gt; has been set to throw on &lt;code&gt;badbit&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;failbit&lt;/code&gt;. By default, streams do not throw on errors — they set error state flags instead. But when you enable exception throwing via &lt;code&gt;exceptions()&lt;/code&gt;, any stream error throws &lt;code&gt;std::ios_base::failure&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdios_basefailure-occurs"&gt;Why std::ios_base::failure Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include reading from an already-exhausted stream, writing to a closed or read-only stream, file I/O errors during stream operations, stream state corruption, and setting &lt;code&gt;exceptions()&lt;/code&gt; to throw on &lt;code&gt;badbit&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;failbit&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>